At this point in time, it is far easier to just rely on CSS extensions well supported by Firefox and Safari, for instance:<p>-moz-border-radius-topleft:		0.4em;
-webkit-border-top-left-radius:		0.4em;
-moz-border-radius-topright:		0.4em;
-webkit-border-top-right-radius:	0.4em;
-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:		0.4em;
-webkit-border-bottom-left-radius:	0.4em;
-moz-border-radius-bottomright:		0.4em;
-webkit-border-bottom-right-radius:	0.4em;<p>This doesn't mess up your HTML with divs, and degrades seamlessly to "not rounded corners" in any other browser.
